[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      377[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Human review queue design.** Entities routed to review (confidence below INCLUDE_THRESHOLD) land in an SQS queue consumed by the review application. This queue requires role-based access control: only credentialed clinical reviewers should see the entity text and context snippets (which contain PHI). Implement IAM policies scoped to a `clinical-reviewers` role. Log every reviewer action (confirm, reclassify, dismiss) to CloudTrail for audit. The audit log must capture who reviewed what, when, and what action they took. This is both a HIPAA minimum-necessary requirement and a model improvement data source: confirmed/reclassified entities become training data for the next model iteration.
